{"questionId":"25909","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows a circle with centre <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>O</mtext></math> and radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math> metres.</p>\n<p>Points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math> lie on the circle and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext><mover><mtext>O</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>B</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></math> radians.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/2fe7f1a34b23cca0c118fe298b7533664f7fd2f2.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the area of the shaded sector.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>let the shaded area be&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math></p>\n<p><strong><br>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt at finding reflex angle&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext><mover><mtext>O</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>B</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3831</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>substitution into area formula&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3831</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow><mrow><m